===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
[[File:Illustration of Tong 同.svg|class=skin-invert-image|thumb|Illustration of Gu 觚]]
{{liushu|p}}: a pipe — original form of {{och-l|筒|pipe}}. {{och-l|*口}} was added later to mark the opening and prevent confusion.

In early forms, {{zh-l|同}} and {{zh-l|*凡}} were distinguished not by the presence of {{zh-l|*口}}, but by symmetry: {{zh-l|同}} is symmetrical, while {{zh-l|凡}} has its right stroke sweeping outward.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=仝,冈,詷,𧇌}}
Perhaps related to {{cog|bo|སྡོང་བ||to unite; to join}}, {{cog|lus|intawng|tr=inᴸ-tɔŋᴴ|t=to meet together; to tally; to agree}}, {{cog|lus|intawn|tr=inᴸ-tɔn<sup>F</sup>|t=to meet together; to tally; to agree}}. Unrelated to {{och-l|叢|to collect; thicket}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

